Syntax for relative CSS selector:
1.-----CSS selector to identify by attribute------
        tagname[attribute='attribute value']
        input[id='first_name']


2.-----CSS selector to identify by ID------
        '#' symbol represents contains ID attribute
        tagname#elementID
        input#first_name


3.-----CSS selector to identify by Class------
        '.' symbol represents class attribute
        tagname.elementID
        input.signup


4.-----CSS selector to identify by contains/sub-string method------
        '*' symbol represents contains/sub-string method
        tagname[attribute *= 'partial attribute value']
        input[placeholder *= 'Email']


5.-----CSS selector to identify by starts-with/prefix method------
        '^' symbol represents starts-with/prefix method in css
        tagname[attribute ^= 'starting attribute value']
        input[type ^= 'password']


6.-----CSS selector to identify by ends-with/suffix method------
        '$' symbol represents ends-with/suffix method in css
        tagname[attribute $= 'ending attribute value']
        img[src $= 'syntax.png']


FOLLOWING CAN BE USED WITH ANY ABOVE TYPE OF XPATH  (AXES Methods)
----CSS selector Concatenate
        tagname[attribute='attribute value'][attribute='attribute value']
        tagname.classValue[attribute='attribute value']
        tagname#idValue[attribute='attribute value']


----Finding child or sub-child elements-----
        *** For direct child we use this symbol '>'
        tagname[@attribute='attribute value'] > tagname[@attribute='attribute value']
        *** For child or sub-child we use space ' '
        tagname[@attribute='attribute value']   tagname[@attribute='attribute value']


----Next sibling elements
        *** For sibling elements we use this symbol '+'
        tagname[@attribute='attribute value'] + tagname[@attribute='attribute value']


*** CSS SELECTOR PSEUDO-CLASSES
1----CSS selector for first child, last child, nth child and nth last child
        tagname[@attribute='attribute value'] : first-child
        tagname[@attribute='attribute value'] : last-child
        tagname[@attribute='attribute value'] : nth-child()
        tagname[@attribute='attribute value'] : nth-last-child()


2----CSS selector for first of type, last of type, nth of type
        tagname[@attribute='attribute value'] > tagname : first-of-type
        tagname[@attribute='attribute value'] > tagname : last-of-type
        tagname[@attribute='attribute value'] > tagname : nth-of-type()